    <!-- What is a Campaign? -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">What is a campaign?</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
          A Campaign in your app is a container for organizing and executing a social media marketing effort. Here's what's inside:
        </p>
        
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Core Attributes:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
          <li><strong>Name & Description</strong> - What the campaign is called and what it's about</li>
          <li><strong>Status</strong> - draft → planning → scheduled → running → paused → completed → failed</li>
          <li><strong>Goal</strong> - awareness, engagement, conversions, traffic, or likes</li>
          <li><strong>Campaign Type</strong> - product_launch, seasonal, brand_awareness, lead_generation, community_building, content_promo, event_promo, user_generated</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Planning:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
          <li><strong>Start/End Dates</strong> - When it runs (default 30 days)</li>
          <li><strong>Target Audience</strong> - Who it's aimed at</li>
          <li><strong>Budget</strong> - Spend limit</li>
          <li><strong>Platforms</strong> - Which social platforms (Instagram, Twitter, Facebook, TikTok, LinkedIn, Pinterest, YouTube)</li>
          <li><strong>Content Pillars</strong> - Themes/topics for content</li>
          <li><strong>Hashtags & Mentions</strong> - Tags to include</li>
          <li><strong>Content Count</strong> - How many posts/images/videos to produce (you get 2 videos and 3 images per campaign)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Execution:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
          <li><strong>Contents</strong> - The actual posts/articles created</li>
          <li><strong>Scheduled Posts</strong> - Posts queued for publishing</li>
          <li><strong>Campaign Tasks</strong> - Individual tasks to execute the campaign</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Metrics:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
          <li><strong>Budget Spent/Remaining</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Content Progress</strong> - % of planned content published</li>
          <li><strong>Engagement Rate</strong> - Likes, comments, shares vs views</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 font-medium">
          In short: A campaign = a time-bound marketing initiative with goals, content plan, platforms, and budget that generates and schedules social media posts automatically.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

